    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (75.02) and **Lawrence Butler** (74.61) headline the lineup as our most potent assets. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** continues to be a cornerstone, benefiting from a favorable wind-out scenario against May, while **Lawrence Butler** finds himself in an ideal spot against Kumar Rocker, buoyed by a significant park factor and a premium leadoff spot. **Taylor Ward** (71.19) and **Tyler Freeman** (71.34) also warrant attention; **Taylor Ward** leverages a strong platoon advantage against the lefty Rodriguez, while **Tyler Freeman** is a calculated play for stolen bases against Spencer Arrighetti, whose slower delivery mechanics provide a subtle edge in our pursuit of scarce SB volume.\n\nThe most difficult exclusion today was **Masyn Winn** (54.70), who hovered near our \"Strong\" tier threshold but was ultimately benched due to a lack of elite ceiling against Cecconi. While **Masyn Winn** is a reliable asset, the offensive environment for our starters\u2014particularly the favorable matchup for **Jonathan Aranda** (68.67) and the lineup positioning of **Cal Raleigh** (68.75)\u2014offered a more compelling combination of run-scoring potential and platoon efficiency. We are also monitoring the lineup status of **Daulton Varsho** (58.53); while he offers marginal value today, his score is depressed by the presence of a pitcher capable of suppressing the run game, making him a high-risk start if the official lineup drops him down the order. \n\nInvestors should remain cautious with **Gleyber Torres** (55.82), whose score sits dangerously close to the marginal threshold. His platoon disadvantage against Lugo significantly caps his ceiling, and he remains our most vulnerable rostered spot. Elsewhere, we are leaning heavily into the platoon edges held by **Jonathan Aranda** and **Brendan Donovan**, both of whom are projected to thrive against Randy V\u00e1squez. We are holding **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Bryson Stott**, **Matt Chapman**, **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve to maximize our daily cap efficiency, ensuring we only deploy starters with high-probability floor outcomes today.",
